- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `nums` must have a size greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 1000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `nums` must be greater than or equal to -100000 and less than or equal to 100000.
- The integer result is the number in the integer array parameter `nums` with the value closest to 0.
- If there are multiple numbers with the same closest distance to 0, the number with the largest value is returned.